      "program_id": "BA_SOCIOLOGY",
      "program_name": "Bachelor of Arts in Sociology",
      "degree_type": "Bachelor of Arts (BA)",
      "school": "School of Humanities and Social Sciences",
      "total_units": 120,
      "description": "Sociology is a cornerstone discipline in the Social Sciences that focuses on the objective study of human societies. The Bachelor of Arts (BA) in Sociology program will prepare learners for a lifetime of change and appreciation of diversity by equipping them with knowledge about human behavior, social organization, culture, and social change as well as teaching them research and writing skills.",
      "learning_outcomes": [
        "Assess social, economic, and political processes using divergent sociological perspectives/theories",
        "Investigate a sociological problem using a range of sociological research strategies and methods of enquiry",
        "Evaluate conceptual, theoretical and applied issues in community development and social welfare",
        "Analyze conceptual, theoretical and applied issues in the sociological study of health and medicine",
        "Analyze conceptual, theoretical and applied issues in sociological study of work and organizations"
      ],
