      "program_id": "BSC_AI_ROBOTICS",
      "program_name": "Bachelor of Science in Artificial Intelligence (AI) & Robotics",
      "degree_type": "Bachelor of Science (BSc)",
      "school": "School of Science & Technology",
      "total_units": 150,
      "description": "The philosophy of the Bachelor of Science in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Robotics is to equip students with advanced knowledge and skills in AI within an intellectually stimulating, culturally diverse, and growth-oriented environment. The program prepares graduates to design and operate a wide range of intelligent systems, including computer vision applications, speech and audio recognition, optical character recognition, computer-aided manufacturing, computer-assisted surgery, autonomous vehicles and drones, intelligent commerce, transport and logistics systems and smart energy solutions.",
      "special_features": [
        "Optional exchange program as an alternative to local internship",
        "Global perspective through international opportunities"
      ],
      "learning_outcomes": [
        "Apply the principles and mechanisms underlying various kinds of intelligent processes, Artificial Intelligence and Robotics systems",
        "Design systems that simulate natural intelligence using Artificial Intelligence and Robotics tools and techniques to solve problems in the society",
        "Develop systems that incorporate Artificial intelligence and Robotics techniques both individually and as a team to solve problems in the society",
        "Managing an AI/robotics project aligned with professional standards",
        "Conduct research on emerging AI/robotics trends, with clear methodology, analysis and conclusions"
      ],
